The paper discusses the design of self-organizing swarms, which involves multiple agents interacting with each other and their environment. This falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the emergence of behaviors in complex systems, which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SY). The use of automation and adaptation in the design process suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.SI).
